Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.44,0:00:09.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kagami Yoshimizu Theater"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.91,0:00:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3rd year, class B...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.08,0:00:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Kuroi!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.20,0:00:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.40,0:00:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The ambiguous 3cm? Does that \Nmean it's plushy? Wait!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The wrapping is a uniform, \Nargh, it's not an act, pooh{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.58,0:00:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gotta do your best, gotta just do it{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.29,0:00:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's time to catch 'n' release, eek{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.91,0:00:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Between sweat (whoop) Sweat (whoop){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.95,0:00:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Darlin', darlin', freeze! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.59,0:00:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kinda lethargic, something's kinda comin' out{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.91,0:00:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I love you... Oh wait, one \Nof those was different{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worrywarts, high metal bars {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.12,0:00:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tasty thoughts... And that's enough!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.91,0:00:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heated body of that flying you-know-who{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.70,0:00:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's what you call a normal girlie{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.22,0:00:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Am I the only one surprised? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.62,0:00:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seconds on pork-bone broth \Nramen with wire-hard noodles{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.77,0:00:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Da da da da da {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.94,0:00:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pom-poms cheer squad{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.66,0:00:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's get cherry pie {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.37,0:00:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happy fun welcoming party {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.01,0:00:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Look up! Sensation{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.45,0:00:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah! Feeling of existence, \Ndot dot small planet{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.41,0:00:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Collided and it melted away, in total awe{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.08,0:01:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go all out to sing, shi-ranger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.97,0:01:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Take it away! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.00,0:01:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I should be the one who'll \Nbe laughing in the end{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.50,0:01:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because I have the sailor suit \N← This is my conclusion{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.51,0:01:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's only Monday! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.70,0:01:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Already in a bad mood? What to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.45,0:01:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I really prefer the summer outfits \N← kya! Wah! Good! (cute!) < 3{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.14,0:01:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Until we approach 3 pixels, \Nno hesitations please ★{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.34,0:01:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do your best, be energetic {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.02,0:01:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My darlin', darlin' please! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.07,0:01:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I'm raising a dog in-game.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.15,0:01:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just so cute that I \Ncan't help but talk to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.45,0:01:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.49,0:01:44.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, for some reason, \Nwhen you speak to animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.87,0:01:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you end up using a really coquettish \Nvoice... even though it's a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.46,0:01:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know what you mean by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I talk to my goldfish, I end \Nup with a really sweet voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.16,0:01:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand doing it for dogs and cats,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.30,0:02:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but talking to fish makes it sound \Nlike you're a really lonely person.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.72,0:02:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?! That's prejudice, damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.22,0:02:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that look of pity in your eyes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.02,0:02:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me of a question \NI've had for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.14,0:02:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Among all the obedience \Ncommands, or rather tricks,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.60,0:02:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can teach a dog, what \Ndoes "chin-chin" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.15,0:02:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... if I go into the details, \Nit will get rather long,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.61,0:02:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'll abbreviate and just \Nsay that it's for certain
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.95,0:02:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the origins of the term \Ncan be traced back to China.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.49,0:02:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, all of you that had naughty \Nthoughts, raise your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.66,0:02:30.71,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"There's Substance in 2-D"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.71,0:02:32.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Study About {\i1}Gu__m{\i0}"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.79,0:02:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, {\i1}Gun__m \N{\i0}is still really popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.46,0:02:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Your dad here loves it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.09,0:02:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's various varieties of it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.72,0:02:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like V and W and X.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.72,0:02:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I've seen every series in real time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.77,0:02:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Call it fan spirit, or a sense of duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.52,0:02:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.31,0:02:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If something like {\i1}G_ndam Serial Murders{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.06,0:02:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or {\i1}Detective Gunda_ {\i0}started, \Nyou'd still watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.61,0:03:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you love {\i1}Gun_am{\i0}... You \Nhave a duty to watch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.95,0:03:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duty?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.70,0:03:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you can't refer to it with a \Nletter, I'm sure it doesn't count.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.91,0:03:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While on the subject of \N{\i1}Gu_dam{\i0}, I just had a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.91,0:03:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sure don't look it, but I'm already \Ntwo years older than _muro now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That really was sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.09,0:03:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in two more years, I'll be \Nthe same age as Mr. Bri__ht.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.59,0:03:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even imagine it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.97,0:03:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know, Mr. Br__ht \Nis rather extreme...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.55,0:03:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even for {\i1}Gun_am{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.81,0:03:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha_an's the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.13,0:03:28.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, since you look more childish \Nthan your actual age, Konata,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have second thoughts about using \Nyou as the basis to judge from.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.94,0:03:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least you could say that I \Nlook younger than my actual age
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.81,0:03:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but you're cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.40,0:03:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got something valuable from our neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.82,0:03:44.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, it's a vacation souvenir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.82,0:03:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? A vase?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.78,0:03:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have grown into a \Ngood girl, just my type!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.50,0:03:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a cute girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.75,0:03:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, it's hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.21,0:03:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, that line sounds rather dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:04.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.84,0:04:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I drank way too much last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.68,0:04:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I thought I'd totally \Npass out until afternoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.22,0:04:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'm still young?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.18,0:04:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now, the morning news \Nfor Monday, July 2...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.18,0:04:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? What happened to Sunday? \NWhere did my holiday go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.32,0:04:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always think about doing my best \Nto study for exams until evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.78,0:04:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't help but get sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.53,0:04:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked Sis about it, and she said...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.58,0:04:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're scared of horror flicks, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.08,0:04:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you watch one, maybe you \Nwon't be able to sleep at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.42,0:04:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other day, you crawled into \Nmy futon after a show like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.54,0:04:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I watched something scary, and \Nsince then I haven't fallen asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.26,0:04:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing like your sister, so to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.23,0:04:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But ever since, at night I get worried
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.47,0:04:49.72,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"CLANG"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.47,0:04:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about what's going on behind me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.72,0:04:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and about every faint sound I hear...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.27,0:04:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's even harder to concentrate \Non studying than it was before!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.69,0:04:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And because of that, I've been losing sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.56,0:05:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,making me really sleepy during class...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.00,0:05:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But despite you saying that \Nyou are scared of such shows,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.44,0:05:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you tend to watch those kinds of \Nthings pretty often, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.24,0:05:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that I want to watch them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.72,0:05:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mother is like that as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.70,0:05:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Miyuki, I rented this. \NWould you like to watch with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.37,0:05:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared to watch it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.17,0:05:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those scared of things like that tend \Nto watch many shows of that type.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They want to see something they're afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.34,0:05:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it, Yuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}! In my \Ncase, I really hate stuff like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.93,0:05:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iwasaki-{\i1}san{\i0}, do you understand this problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.06,0:05:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking that one over myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.06,0:05:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If a little more thought doesn't do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.10,0:05:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to ask Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.69,0:05:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. We're lucky that we both have \Nreliable upperclassmen so close to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.03,0:05:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was what Iwasaki-{\i1}san {\i0}and I were \Ntalking about at school today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.57,0:05:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? She's relying on me that much?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.99,0:05:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's going to personally experience \Nthe harshness of reality later on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:05:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.67,0:06:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, did you ever study for \Nexams together with Bro Ki?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.30,0:06:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.26,0:06:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a popular situation in games \Nand stuff, but when a boy and a girl
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.55,0:06:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who get along well are together, there's no \Nway they'd be able to concentrate, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.64,0:06:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you're not concentrating, you \Nstart fantasizing about what you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.93,0:06:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm seeing withdrawal symptoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, there's something that \NI want you to teach me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.90,0:06:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kinda cornered with my own \Nstudying now, so can you ask Sis Yui?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.40,0:06:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Study, gotta study.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.07,0:06:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a dirty trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.45,0:06:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to a different school... \NI didn't learn this at my school!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.66,0:06:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.62,0:06:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.16,0:06:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm stuck myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.84,0:06:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, do you understand this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.75,0:06:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course you wouldn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.21,0:06:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask if you're not \Nrelying on me for an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.34,0:06:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't you here for the \Nconversation I had earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.76,0:06:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I wonder if I should just \Ncall Miyuki-{\i1}san {\i0}and ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.18,0:06:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I'm sure it would bother her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.81,0:06:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, I think she'd be bothered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.35,0:06:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, it's late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.39,0:07:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are parents written out of the game \Nfrom the start at times like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.27,0:07:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like her to rely on me every so often...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.52,0:07:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll correct that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.48,0:07:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izumi! Don't go falling asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this day and age where \Ncorporal punishment is banned,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.99,0:07:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you really punch people on a regular basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.99,0:07:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that it bothers me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.83,0:07:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True. But it's not just anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.79,0:07:21.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do choose who I hit, in a lot of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.21,0:07:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It gets to be a pain later on, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.50,0:07:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, she clearly admitted it... That's \Nanother amazing part about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.09,0:07:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place, the banning \Nof corporal punishment is absurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.46,0:07:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's the end of class.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.88,0:07:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, I'm sorry, I don't \Nunderstand the era titles and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.35,0:07:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}, teach me this problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.35,0:07:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of you with "Takara, Takara!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.39,0:07:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you come ask your teacher \Nabout things you don't understand?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.02,0:07:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Kuroi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.94,0:07:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Izumi, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.77,0:07:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there was something \Nthat I wanted to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.58,0:07:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? You can ask me anything, \Ngo ahead, ask, it's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.07,0:07:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about a rare item in the \Ngame that I'm playing right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.03,0:07:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait... Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.99,0:08:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it! That's \Nnot what I want to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.04,0:08:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really hot after a typhoon's passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.17,0:08:11.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had a lot of typhoons this \Nyear, so of course they're past.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.09,0:08:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what was good?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.89,0:08:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask just to be on the safe side... \NYou were making a joke earlier, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.27,0:08:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, there's something I \Nwant to ask you, Sis...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.90,0:08:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? You're being so formal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.40,0:08:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About this morning... Did \NKona-{\i1}chan {\i0}say something strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.45,0:08:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't see anything wrong \Nabout what she said, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.74,0:08:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She watches the news with me, but \Nwhy is she at Konata's level?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.82,0:09:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does their timing always make \Nme think they're aiming for this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.39,0:09:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pitcher is looking out for \Nthe runner on second base...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.68,0:09:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on with the \Nbaseball broadcast today?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.69,0:09:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, at this rate, it looks \Nlike it'll run long.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.90,0:09:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again? Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.82,0:09:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to reprogram the timer recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.03,0:09:13.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.24,0:09:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't they just reserve a longer \Nslot for the game to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.86,0:09:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.24,0:09:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,professional baseball is really \Nslow with each and every movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.79,0:09:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the players did all their \Nmovements in a lively manner,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.33,0:09:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,couldn't they shorten the game time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.21,0:09:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, those who like it like everything \Nabout it, including things like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.29,0:09:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they're concentrating \Nmentally or something, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.34,0:09:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is it? Are you used to school life now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.93,0:09:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but there's lots of homework \Nand stuff, so it's very hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.97,0:09:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.85,0:09:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seniors concentrate mainly \Non entrance exam preparation,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.15,0:09:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so there's not much homework, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.73,0:09:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konata... you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.11,0:10:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whew, it's so hot out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.41,0:10:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konata! What are you thinking, \Nwalking around like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.91,0:10:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do \Nif Yu-{\i1}chan {\i0}mimics you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.00,0:10:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's been hot out lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.42,0:10:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, it's that thing \Nthey do at the Diet, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.46,0:10:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Cool Biz"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.59,0:10:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.21,0:10:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's a bit different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.01,0:10:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What have you been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.30,0:10:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering when I'd receive a \Nreply to a text message I sent...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.81,0:10:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it bother you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.34,0:10:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was reading a book, \Nand missed my station...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.39,0:10:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As always, Miyuki-{\i1}san{\i0}, your \Nnonchalant clumsiness is so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.69,0:10:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think so? I think \Nit would just be a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.90,0:10:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.53,0:10:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The shameful look in trying to patch \Nthings up is where you find {\i1}moe{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.07,0:10:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's cuter to have a couple of flaws!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.91,0:10:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? So, when you're at work, you're like...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.33,0:10:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I spilled that. I'm \Nterribly sorry about it, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.83,0:10:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.96,0:10:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kagami... You look a bit stupid, \Nyou know? What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.34,0:10:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a conversation topic you brought up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.47,0:10:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I was the one that did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.93,0:11:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so? Do you do clumsy things as \Nwell, to gain those kinds of points?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.81,0:11:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't do stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.31,0:11:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There might be some prejudice about \Nit, but the manager would scold me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.23,0:11:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Knowing you, I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.11,0:11:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'd do it and say "That stuff is \Nso {\i1}moe{\i0}," or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.52,0:11:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get it, Kagami.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that clumsy girls are \Ncute, and there is {\i1}moe {\i0}there,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.72,0:11:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if it does damage in real life, \Nit's rather irritating, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.62,0:11:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's something that you \Nlaugh at and let go in games.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.24,0:11:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otaku are really harsh \Nabout things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.91,0:11:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once again, if we have a contestant \Nwith a perfect score today,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.08,0:11:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,courtesy of Look JTB,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.79,0:11:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll give away a one month tundra- \Ntour package to a lucky viewer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.54,0:11:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Variety shows and quiz shows like \Nthis often have prizes, and cash too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.64,0:11:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's because you get \Nmore contestants when you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.43,0:11:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if a popular celebrity comes for \Nit, they can get better ratings!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.56,0:11:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, though I don't know the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.52,0:11:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.47,0:12:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they made the viewers \Nable to join the quiz,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.99,0:12:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and tilt the prize money \Ntowards the viewer entries,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.20,0:12:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,don't you think the ratings \Nwould go up even more?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.70,0:12:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I kinda think that way, but you have \Na very straightforward appeal there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.02,0:12:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.08,0:12:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S'up?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.50,0:12:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking while \Nplaying a game yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.08,0:12:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but who is the school idol at our school?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.96,0:12:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? A school idol? You mean \Nsomething like "Miss Ryouou"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.89,0:12:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, something like that. Normally, \Nyou'd see something of that sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.05,0:12:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, in games, you'd have \Nsomething like groupies and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.46,0:12:41.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired again today!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.57,0:12:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So refreshing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.74,0:12:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I have the early shift tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.78,0:12:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I won't connect to the 'net \Ntonight, and just go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.70,0:12:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's bad if I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.42,0:13:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Securing hours of sleep first \Nis a sign that I'm aging...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.46,0:13:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was still in school, I'd shave \Noff hours of sleep for my hobbies...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.43,0:13:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.77,0:13:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamura-{\i1}san{\i0}, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.02,0:13:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been doing all sorts \Nof things for a while now...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.90,0:13:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, when you draw, you \Nknow how you end up with
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.17,0:13:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the same facial expression as \Nthe character you're drawing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... So you were drawing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.20,0:13:33.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know that you \Ndrew manga, Tamura-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.37,0:13:35.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though it's mainly {\i1}doujin{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.55,0:13:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of manga do you draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.63,0:13:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, normal four-panel comic strips...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.63,0:13:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or romance manga between my \Nfavorite game characters...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.97,0:13:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is so hard to answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.01,0:13:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lottery ticket that I bought \Nthe other day on a trial basis
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.39,0:13:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was a winner for 3,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.85,0:13:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I thought that I was in luck \Nfrom early in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.94,0:14:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.61,0:14:05.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But on my way here, my bicycle got a flat \Ntire and it costs money to repair it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.40,0:14:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I had to buy a lunch at the store \Nto replace the one I dropped...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.82,0:14:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like it was planned to be, the \N3,000 yen cleanly left my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.58,0:14:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Truth is stranger than fiction, they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.32,0:14:18.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.09,0:14:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably good fodder for manga, \Nso I'm thinking that it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.63,0:14:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So tough...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.22,0:14:31.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Thunderous roar"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.89,0:14:39.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Roar"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.90,0:14:42.31,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Thud"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.90,0:14:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To an artist, her writing \Nhand is like her life...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.70,0:14:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is one thing that I need \Nto risk my life to save...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.66,0:14:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So tough...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.45,0:14:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, just as I thought, you're \Nreally good, Tamura-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.96,0:15:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I've been in a slump \Nlately... That's a failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.17,0:15:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but of what I've recently done, \NI think this one went pretty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.67,0:15:10.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Objection!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.55,0:15:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Often, the \Nperson looking at art doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.10,0:15:19.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,understand where the artist is being \Npicky, or the subtleties in the art.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.43,0:15:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew that, I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.89,0:15:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, drat!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.73,0:15:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Tamura-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.40,0:15:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My favorite mechanical pencil!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.57,0:15:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was drawing yesterday, and left \Nit on top of my desk back home!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.20,0:15:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I lend you one?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.49,0:15:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it has to be that one, or rather, \Nhow it draws is totally different...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.54,0:15:44.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, mechanical \Npencils are all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.42,0:15:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know that. I knew \Nyou'd react that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.34,0:15:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, I got lost, and couldn't \Nget out for three hours...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.93,0:15:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Tamura-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.93,0:16:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So embarrassing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.23,0:16:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are they thinking, to \Ndress like that on the streets?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.56,0:16:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coats?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.48,0:16:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! Aren't they hot, dressing \Nlike that in the summer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.82,0:16:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this pain is only for those in the know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.95,0:16:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a sec, I'm going to text a friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.33,0:16:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.24,0:16:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, it's crowded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.75,0:16:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to put our names down on the sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.71,0:16:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I ended up playing games \Nwith Sis until really late...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.50,0:16:30.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Suzaku? Miss Suzaku, party of three?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.21,0:16:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're calling us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.13,0:16:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Tamura-{\i1}san{\i0}, that was a different name...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.04,0:16:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, I feel like writing down \Nthe name of my favorite character.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.10,0:16:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just want to feel the character \Nclose to you or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.11,0:16:51.82,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Haruhi" "Kyon" "Yuki" "Mikuru" \N"Itsuki" "Current turn: Haruhi"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.82,0:16:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There really are people like \Nme around everywhere I go...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.87,0:17:03.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Letter from the Nurse's Office"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.57,0:17:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.04,0:17:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could be slender and \Ntall like you, Iwasaki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.63,0:17:19.93,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fantasy"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.63,0:17:18.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minami-{\i1}chan{\i0}, I guess you can say that \Nyou're someone I admire... so...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.39,0:17:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yutaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:30.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Reality"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.14,0:17:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kobayakawa-{\i1}san{\i0}, I'm sure you'll still grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.77,0:17:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps you'll end up taller than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.67,0:17:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More than you, Iwasaki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.77,0:17:32.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fantasy"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.11,0:17:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minami-{\i1}chan{\i0}... Minami-{\i1}chan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.93,0:17:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minami-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.28,0:17:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! That is the law of the land, so no!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.83,0:17:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, the last one \Nis obviously different!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.83,0:17:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.34,0:17:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamura-{\i1}san{\i0}, are you all right? \NYou seem a bit pale...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.84,0:17:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, the submission deadline \Nfor the upcoming event was today...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.42,0:18:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sent out the manuscript I worked on \Nall night via courier this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.51,0:18:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but when I'm working so \Ndesperately for something,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.85,0:18:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I'm shining from within...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.23,0:18:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So tough!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.40,0:18:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamura-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.87,0:18:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is {\i1}yaoi{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.78,0:18:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which meaning are you asking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.37,0:18:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Star{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.50,0:18:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lucky Channel{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.17,0:18:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning Luckies!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.91,0:18:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time passes by quickly, this is already \Nthe 19th episode of {\i1}Lucky Channel{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.42,0:18:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's starting to feel like we're \Nfinally nearing the climax!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.42,0:18:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Akira Kogami, your navigator!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.43,0:18:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm Minoru Shiraishi, her \Nassistant. My best regards.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.85,0:18:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, Akira-{\i1}sama{\i0}, you \Nseem to be in a fine mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.85,0:18:51.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Helper helper submarine, \Nsomething good's gonna happen! ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.44,0:18:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something wonderful happen to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.69,0:18:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think something has?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.15,0:18:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.28,0:18:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.61,0:19:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, being on TV really wears on one's nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.32,0:19:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fatigue builds up after 19 episodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I want to \Ntake it slow and unwind,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.74,0:19:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,soaking in a hot spring or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.37,0:19:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if I can't get something \Nlike that vacation prize,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.46,0:19:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like the quiz show in the main show.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.92,0:19:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you have to start by becoming \Na contestant on that quiz show.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.80,0:19:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but vacations are so \Nnice! I'd like to go myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.85,0:19:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you travel through lands you \Ndon't know, it clears the soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.60,0:19:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing better!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.94,0:19:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You like to travel?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.27,0:19:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, of course! I love it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.52,0:19:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've actually gone to all \Nsorts of places, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.77,0:19:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I climbed up Mt. Takao, and I \Nhad that trip to Jougashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.28,0:19:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an outdoor kind of guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.99,0:19:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you like to travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.12,0:19:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, I think strolls in \Nthe woods calm your nerves,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.95,0:19:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with Mother Nature all around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.96,0:19:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's wonderful. Mother \NNature, a stroll in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.50,0:19:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It calms your nerves down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.50,0:19:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it just?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.54,0:20:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Far from the noise of the city, \Nleaving your body to quiet nature!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.88,0:20:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It soothes both the body and the mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.18,0:20:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good. Isn't Mother Nature wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.64,0:20:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think Mother Nature is wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.18,0:20:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to go for a stroll in the woods?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.93,0:20:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious? Can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.14,0:20:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no, if I can, I'll go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.94,0:20:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, then, it's been decided... \NMinoru's Mother Nature Tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.90,0:20:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.37,0:20:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.86,0:20:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they have what you wish they had.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.95,0:20:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.16,0:20:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I going?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.12,0:20:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mt. Fuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.66,0:20:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, but I've already \Nbeen up a mountain once...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.91,0:20:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Not the mountain itself, \Nbut the big forest at its base.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.00,0:20:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to go into Fuji Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.37,0:20:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see, the forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.71,0:20:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who? Oh, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.55,0:20:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.63,0:20:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, so after getting there, what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.69,0:20:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go scoop up some water.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.60,0:20:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.22,0:20:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to drink the famous Fuji \Nwater, so get some from the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.85,0:20:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding! You can just buy \Nit in convenience stores and stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.44,0:20:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want it fresh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.48,0:21:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be alone, right? Alone? {\i1}Alone{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.73,0:21:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone is going to come with me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.57,0:21:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right, you'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.15,0:21:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The director and producer will \Nsacrifice themselves to go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.03,0:21:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you glad?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.99,0:21:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, don't you just waste time there!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.99,0:21:12.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.50,0:21:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cross the line between life and death!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.37,0:21:14.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.33,0:21:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's already this late?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.42,0:21:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, we'll have a lovely guest \Nfor the next episode of {\i1}Lucky Channel{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.34,0:21:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look forward to it! Bye-nee!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.38,0:21:28.26,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch, ouch, ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.85,0:21:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't have to have an excuse \Nto drive him out, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.93,0:21:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just hurry up and ch--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.43,0:21:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ A portion of my body is hot! Hot! ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.10,0:21:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello there! This is Minoru Shiraishi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.27,0:21:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I'd like you to listen: {\i1}Otokono \NIkizama {\i0}({\i1}The Life of a Man{\i0})!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.07,0:21:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Hah, I want to be just like that guy ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.75,0:22:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Plunging forward looking \Nonly in front of you ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.42,0:22:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Once you make a decision, \Nas far as you can go ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.47,0:22:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Oh, once you bite \Ndown, you don't let go ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.44,0:22:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Oh, soft-shelled turtle, soft-shelled \Nturtle, soft-shelled turtle! ♪
